The case against four people accused of killing a Limpopo police officer has been postponed. Sisters Nyambeni and Khathutshelo Nemugumoni appeared in the Vuwani Magistrate’s Court on Friday to face charges of murder and conspiracy to commit murder alongside siblings Khathutshelo and Calvin Tshisudi. The four will appear in court again on 2 March for a formal bail application. Alugumi Thomas Nemugumoni was fatally stabbed on 12 February while arriving at his home in Tshakhuma from work. -TNA Reporter